"**FORMAT_MAX** = **39** --- Represents the size of the :ref:`Format "
"<enum_Image_Format>` enum."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:336
msgid "enum **Interpolation**:"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:338
msgid ""
"**INTERPOLATE_NEAREST** = **0** --- Performs nearest-neighbor "
"interpolation. If the image is resized, it will be pixelated."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:340
msgid ""
"**INTERPOLATE_BILINEAR** = **1** --- Performs bilinear interpolation. If "
"the image is resized, it will be blurry. This mode is faster than "
":ref:`INTERPOLATE_CUBIC <class_Image_constant_INTERPOLATE_CUBIC>`, but it"
" results in lower quality."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:342
msgid ""
"**INTERPOLATE_CUBIC** = **2** --- Performs cubic interpolation. If the "
"image is resized, it will be blurry. This mode often gives better results"
" compared to :ref:`INTERPOLATE_BILINEAR "
"<class_Image_constant_INTERPOLATE_BILINEAR>`, at the cost of being "
"slower."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:344
msgid ""
"**INTERPOLATE_TRILINEAR** = **3** --- Performs bilinear separately on the"
" two most-suited mipmap levels, then linearly interpolates between them."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:346
msgid ""
"It's slower than :ref:`INTERPOLATE_BILINEAR "
"<class_Image_constant_INTERPOLATE_BILINEAR>`, but produces higher-quality"
" results with much less aliasing artifacts."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:348
msgid ""
"If the image does not have mipmaps, they will be generated and used "
"internally, but no mipmaps will be generated on the resulting image."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:350
msgid ""
"**Note:** If you intend to scale multiple copies of the original image, "
"it's better to call :ref:`generate_mipmaps "
"<class_Image_method_generate_mipmaps>`] on it in advance, to avoid "
"wasting processing power in generating them again and again."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:352
msgid ""
"On the other hand, if the image already has mipmaps, they will be used, "
"and a new set will be generated for the resulting image."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_image.rst:354
msgid ""
"**INTERPOLATE_LANCZOS** = **4** --- Performs Lanczos interpolation. This "
"is the slowest image resizing mode, but it typically gives the best "
"results, especially when downscalng images."
msgstr ""

